Package: atlas-voice
Version: 1.0.2
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Architecture: amd64
Depends: python3, gir1.2-ayatanaappindicator3-0.1, xdotool, xclip, libnotify-bin, pulseaudio-utils, wget
Installed-Size: 2560000
Maintainer: Brian Kelley <briankelley@users.noreply.github.com>
Description: Always-listening voice dictation with wake word detection
 Atlas Voice provides hands-free voice dictation using OpenWakeWord
 for wake word detection and OpenAI Whisper for transcription.
 .
 Say "Hey Atlas" to activate, dictate your text, and say "break"
 to finish. Text is automatically typed into the focused application.
 .
 Features:
  - Custom trained "Hey Atlas" wake word
  - GPU-accelerated Whisper large-v3 transcription
  - System tray icon with pause/resume/disable controls
  - Automatic silence detection
  - Spoken punctuation support
 .
 System requirements:
  - NVIDIA GPU with 4GB+ VRAM (CUDA acceleration)
  - ~4GB disk space (installed) + ~3GB for Whisper model (auto-downloaded)
  - Working microphone
  - Desktop environment with system tray support
 .
 All Python dependencies are bundled in an isolated virtual environment.
 The Whisper large-v3 model (~3GB) is downloaded automatically from
 huggingface.co/Systran during installation.
